The Splitting Path~
The single trail here fractures into three, none of them marked, each curving away into trees that seem to lean inward to block the view.  The soil at the junction is disturbed — wide, dragging marks suggest something heavy was recently moved or moved itself through here, though toward which of the three branches is impossible to determine.  A smell of iron lingers, partially masked by the ever-present rot, and a spray of dark fluid on a low branch has dried to a rust-brown crust.~
