The Blighted Rise~
The ground here lifts into a low ridge, giving a rare vantage over the surrounding forest canopy — or it would, if the canopy were not closed overhead in a seamless ceiling of intertwined black branches.  The ridge's crest is bare of undergrowth, the soil hard and pale grey, cracked in polygonal plates like dried mud at the bottom of a dead lake.  From this slight height, the sheer scale of the Withered Depths becomes apparent: in every direction, as far as the eye can follow between the trunks, the forest shows the same character of deep, patient, total corruption.~
