The Sentinel Pines~
Three enormous pine trees stand in a rough triangle here, their trunks wider than a man is tall, their needles long since replaced by fine black filaments that catch the light like hair.  The space between them has a cathedral quality — the scale of the trees dwarfs the surrounding forest, and their interlocked canopy blocks out everything but a few thin columns of dim purple light.  Something has stripped the bark from each trunk at about seven feet of height, leaving raw pale wood exposed in a horizontal band that encircles all three trees like a shared scar.~
