#1012
The Shrouded Pit~
A natural pit cuts into the forest floor here, perhaps ten feet deep and wide enough to lose a horse in, its bottom invisible beneath a thick column of grey-white mist that sits in it as though poured.  The mist doesn't flow or shift — it hangs utterly static, slightly warmer than the surrounding air, and carries a faint sweet smell that is almost pleasant and therefore deeply wrong in this place.  The trees around the pit's rim have all grown away from it, their trunks leaning outward as though recoiling over decades from whatever the pit contains.~
