#1015
The Sunken Threshold~
The descent through the crumbling arch ends here in a rough chamber whose ceiling is the underside of the forest floor, pierced by roots that dangle like ropes in various stages of decay.  The transition from open air to enclosed earth is abrupt and total: sound is swallowed immediately, the constant background noise of the forest above replaced by an underground silence broken only by the faint drip of moisture and the distant, barely audible sound of something vast slowly respiring.  The walls are packed earth braced by enormous root-buttresses, and every surface has been colonised by @@pfungal growth@@N in shades of purple, grey, and a deep, arterial red.  The passage back up is sealed by the crumbling arch's mechanism above.~
