The Tangled Root Chamber~
An enormous root-mass dominates this chamber, a tangle of roots from multiple trees above that have grown into each other in the dark and formed a solid knot the size of a carriage, suspended between floor and ceiling by their own structural tension.  The space around it is cramped and requires navigation — ducking here, stepping over a ground-level root there — but the knot itself is strangely beautiful, its surface worn smooth by whatever brushes past it, every groove and join caught by the bioluminescent glow in a play of shadow and cold light.  A faint groan issues from the knot at irregular intervals as the roots above shift their weight.~
