The Pale Gallery~
This passage has a different quality than those nearby — the walls are pale, almost white, the earth here packed to a chalk-like hardness and seamed with thin veins of actual mineral.  The bioluminescence is almost absent, and the lighting comes instead from a sparse scattering of small, very bright white fungi growing in evenly spaced clusters along the ceiling.  The overall effect is of a well-lit gallery or library corridor, clinical in its brightness, which makes the row of bones embedded in the far wall — arranged with evident purpose, pressed into the white earth in a long horizontal line — all the more striking.~
